values:
For the last few years all of my goals, thoughts, and plans revolved around two or three central ideas. Recently, I realized that way of thinking is getting me absolutely nowhere. 

I work hard in school and try to get good grades; am I any closer to graduating? No.
I work two jobs to help pay for this schooling, and one of the jobs is supposed to help me in my career. Am I any closer to this career? No.
Do I even really want to be a teacher? No.
I put in five years of love and devotion and selflessness into a relationship. Am I any closer to getting married? No.
I make most of my decisions based on my possible future with this person. Do I get the same consideration? No.

Nothing in my life has really changed in the last five years. Everything is the same. I've been working for change, willing it to happen, doing everything I can to make some kind of transformation in my life; but still, nothing. I have watched the lives change of everyone around me. People graduate, start their careers, get engaged, move out, get married, etc. I'm stuck in the same place. I feel immobile. 

I need to reverse my thinking. My goals and plans should involve only me, without empty reliance on others. I need to make things happen. Perhaps I should cancel out all my goals and just live day-to-day. Maybe I should go to Europe for a month or two. Maybe I should quit school and travel. I could get a full time job and move out of my house. Anything. I need change. 

I have the most monotonous life in the world. My life does not make me happy. I guess it's up to me, and only me, to change things around. I'm tired to being me; I want to try someone else on for size because being me clearly isn't working out.
I haven't forgotten about my boycott of your happiness. It's still banned. I'm still on strike. Don't forget it.

For the past few months, I have felt extremely blue. A lot is happening. My crazy sister wants to get married to a guy no one has met and move away, leaving me all by myself. My dad hasn't been well and is getting a really scary heart surgery, and I don't really know how to feel about it. Should I be happy that he's getting something done that may help, or should I be scared that it won't work, just like the last ones didn't?
I feel like I'm standing still when everything inside of me is screaming for me to progress forward. I want to be proactive, I want to propel into my future. I want to graduate this year and be able to pursue a career. I want to be move out of my house and I want to be married. I'm not saying I need all of these things to happen right now, but I feel like none of these things are going to happen EVER. I feel like I'm just stagnant. A lot of my friends are finishing school this year, but I had to take time off because of transferring, plus I changed my major twice, so I still have at least another year after this one. My close friend, Becky, and I made plans to move out together next September, but she's getting married that month so I don't think that'll work out. She's really the only friend I can imagine living with (besides the one that lives in PA) I always considered myself to be a motivated person, and I've never been content with being unsuccessful. I feel like I'm only happy when I'm getting something done or when I feel like I just did something worth while. I haven't done anything to be proud of in quite some time, and it doesn't seem like anything new is going to happen any time soon. I'm just stuck. I'm stuck where I am. I'm UNHAPPY, and I have been for quite sometime. 
So, now is the time. It's time to make things happen. It's time to take as many classes as I can, work two jobs, and get things done. I can feel more content with taking longer to graduate if I know I'm doing everything I can do get there. It's time to question where my life is heading. If I'm in dead end situations, it's time to GET OUT! I'm so done with living in the now. It's just not who I am. I want to live for the future. It's time that I make my self happy again. I deserve that.
The only reason I'm even writing this is because I need to let it out, but I really have nobody to talk to about it. My best friend lives far away and is really hard to get a hold of. My friends here all seem like they're really happy and they're moving forward and making advances. While I am happy for them and proud of them, I feel weird talking to them about how UNhappy and UNsuccessful I am. I especially feel weird telling anyone about my dad, because they either have nothing to say (who knows what to say, really?) or they say something stupid. (like, won't that ruin his new tattoo?) I can't talk to Mark about it, because I feel like it's insensitive or something. I also can't talk to Mark about moving forward because he has NO IDEA what I mean. He lives for the now, he's content not making any future plans and doesn't understand why I need to set goals and make those types of plans. I feel lost and lonely and like I'm failing in life.
I need to make things happen.... here's hoping
24/7 Christmas songs started a day early this year. Someone must have done it for me, because I've put feeling extra blue lately, and it put me in a slightly better mood.

When I say, "I am a Christian,"  I'm not shouting, "I've been saved!"
I'm whispering, "I get lost!  That's why I chose this way"

When I say, "I am a Christian,"  I don't speak with human pride
I'm confessing that I stumble-needing God to be my guide

When I say, "I am a Christian,"  I'm not trying to be strong
I'm professing that I'm weak and pray for strength to carry on

When I say, "I am a Christian," I'm not bragging of success
I'm admitting that I've failed and cannot ever pay the debt

When I say, "I am a Christian,"  I don't think I know it all
I submit to my confusion asking humbly to be taught

When I say, "I am a Christian," I'm not claiming to be perfect
My flaws are far too visible but God believes I'm worth it

When I say, "I am a Christian,"  I still feel the sting of pain
I have my share of heartache which is why I seek His name

When I say, "I am a Christian,"  I do not wish to judge
I have no authority--I only know I'm loved

Two more couples that I know are getting married. Both have only been dating their significant other for a two years. True to my promise, i refuse to be happy for them. I will not participate in love-type celebrations. I don't know why everyone thought I was kidding.

Today, Mark and I watched TV together and just laid next to each other, cuddling. We were joking around with each other and looking into each other's eyes. It was the happiest I've been in a long time.
